description:
A government forest where you are allowed to pitch two tents over one night. The tents must be no bigger than 3 person each. Not much else to say about the place.

Check the website. You can find English language in the menu and all other forests approved for pitching a tent in Denmark at: https://naturstyrelsen.dk/naturoplevelser/overnatning/fri-teltning/#{"x":671157,"y":6240022,"zoom":2}

Watch out for ticks! There are plenty of them. I just walked 20 meters and back and found five crawling on my legs. Use repellent.

Large parking lot. free parking during daytime( overnight only campers and vans and cost 110dkk /15euro
) free toilets, hot showers 10dkk ( cold showers outside is free)
right next to ocean and shopping in town.
